$ %APPDATA%

The typical path for the folder that is identified by the → Windows/development/environment-variables[environment variable] `%APPDATA%` is `C:\Users\username\Appdata\Roaming`.

Files that are specific to a machine rather than a → Windows/user-account/domain[domain] go into → Windows/dirs/Users/username/AppData/Local[`%LOCALAPPDATA%`].

Some subdirectories that might be found below `%APPDATA%` include
  • Adobe
  • dvdcss
  • → Windows/dirs/Users/username/AppData/Roaming/gnupg[gnupg]
  • → Windows/dirs/Users/username/AppData/Roaming/IrfanView[IrfanView]
  • LibreOffice
  • MacroMedia
  • → Windows/dirs/Users/username/AppData/Roaming/Microsoft[Microsoft]
  • NuGet
  • → Windows/dirs/Users/username/AppData/Roaming/Mozilla[Mozilla]
  • Stellarium
  • → Windows/dirs/Users/username/AppData/Roaming/sqldeveloper[sqldeveloper]
  • → Windows/dirs/Users/username/AppData/Roaming/Windows[Windows]
  • vlc

sa:

  The → Microsoft/dot-net enumeration → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/Environment/SpecialFolder[`System.Environment+SpecialFolder`].

  The parent directory → Windows/dirs/Users/username/AppData
